28/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu held a news conference Friday (25 July) to review highlights of his first year in office. 
He said he has focused on building "the real image of a president, who represents the unity of the people and who is loyal to the constitution". 
Moisiu said he is committed to maintaining dialogue by organising roundtables with the political parties on key issues, such as property and election reforms. 
He also reiterated his commitment to fighting organised crime, corruption and bureaucracy while enhancing regional co-operation and measures that will bring the country closer to EU and NATO membership. 
(ATA, BBC - 25/07/03)
